news.title: HSBC takes extra space in Canary Wharf due to HQ squeeze
news.para: HSBC has leased additional office space at 40 Bank Street in Canary Wharf due to insufficient room at its future headquarters near St Paul's Cathedral. This decision provides a boost to Canary Wharf, which has faced declining office values and planned departures.

news.title: Tesla India takes on lease 8,200 sq ft commercial space in Delhi's Aerocity
news.para: Tesla is expanding its Indian footprint, leasing 8,200 sq ft of commercial space in Delhi's Aerocity for Rs 17.22 lakh monthly, with a 9-year lease and rent increases every three years.

news.title: Varmora Granito files IPO papers with Sebi, eyes ₹400 crore via fresh issue
news.para: Varmora Granito Ltd, a tiles and bathware manufacturer, has filed for an IPO with Sebi to raise funds through a fresh issue of shares worth Rs 400 crore and an OFS of 5.24 crore equity shares. The company intends to use the proceeds to repay borrowings and for general corporate purposes.
